line: [emcee] Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to Kavin Jay: Everybody Calm Down!
[crowd cheering] Now, please put your hands together
for the guy whose name is in the title,
Kavin Jay!
[loud applause]
[crowd cheering]
[upbeat music playing]
Singapore, how are you guys doing?
[audience cheering]
Oh, yeah, it's a lot... It took a lot of balls.
It took a lot of balls for a Malaysian guy to shoot his special
in Singapore.
Oh, this is gonna be... You guys look beautiful. All right, uh...
Singaporeans, make some noise!
[crowd cheering]
Malaysians, make some noise!

It's such a beautiful phrase, right?
A lot of emcees use it, a lot of, uh, you know, comedians use it.
But it's one of those things where I find it to be very Asian.
Right? Because y'all did all the work.
You all bought the tickets.
You all braved the jam.

maybe I should lead a healthier lifestyle.

Now, I had a show in Manila, right?

Thank you for laughing at my impending diabetes.

I really like wearing clothes.
